Introduction

Bae Jin Young is a South Korean singer. He is a former member of the boy group CIX and the project boy group Wanna One.

Jinyoung was first known for participating in Mnet's 2017 survival program Produce 101 Season 2. He managed to earn himself the final place in the group Wanna One by finishing in 10th place. Jinyoung made his anticipated debut as a lead dancer and visual of the group on August 7, 2017, with the mini album 1X1=1 (To Be One). He continued to be in Wanna One until they concluded their activities on January 27, 2019. However, the group reunited to release the single Beautiful (Part.3) on January 27, 2022.

He debuted as a soloist on April 26, 2019, with the single "Hard To Say Goodbye".

3 months after his solo debut, Jinyoung debuted as the lead vocalist, center, and face of the boy group CIX on July 23, 2019, with the group's first mini album "HELLO Chapter 1: Hello, Stranger". On August 5, 2024, C9 Entertainment announced that Jinyoung had terminated his contract with the company on August 1, 2024, and would be leaving CIX.
